<h2>Events Management</h2>

<h3>Available Operations</h3>
<div class="endpoint">
  <span class="method get">GET</span>
  <code>/api/events</code>
  - Retrieve all events
</div>
<div class="endpoint">
  <span class="method post">POST</span>
  <code>/api/events</code>
  - Create a new event (authentication required)
</div>

<h3>Event Details</h3>
<p>For specific events:</p>
<div class="endpoint">
  <span class="method get">GET</span>
  <code>/api/events/:id</code>
  - Get event details by ID
</div>
<div class="endpoint">
  <span class="method put">PUT</span>
  <code>/api/events/:id</code>
  - Update event (owner only)
</div>
<div class="endpoint">
  <span class="method delete">DELETE</span>
  <code>/api/events/:id</code>
  - Delete event (owner only)
</div>

<h2>Event Properties</h2>
<p>Events have the following properties:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>id</strong>: Unique identifier</li>
  <li><strong>title</strong>: Event title</li>
  <li><strong>description</strong>: Event description</li>
  <li><strong>date</strong>: Event date and time</li>
  <li><strong>location</strong>: Event location</li>
  <li><strong>organizer</strong>: User ID of the organizer</li>
  <li><strong>createdAt</strong>: Creation timestamp</li>
  <li><strong>updatedAt</strong>: Last update timestamp</li>
</ul>

<h2>Example Event Creation</h2>
<pre><code>{ "title": "Tech Conference 2024", "description": "Annual technology
    conference", "date": "2024-12-01T10:00:00Z", "location": "Convention Center"
    }</code></pre>

<h2>Authentication</h2>
<p>Creating, updating, or deleting events requires authentication. Include the
  JWT token in the Authorization header:</p>
<pre><code>Authorization: Bearer your-jwt-token-here</code></pre>